You'd cut off their hair?

457
00:35:59,000 --> 00:35:59,999
Yes, they need it!

458
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:00,999
What do you think about
what they’re doing?

459
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:01,999
Well, it's all very childish...

460
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:02,500
It's childish?

461
00:36:02,700 --> 00:36:03,100
Yes, it is.

462
00:36:04,900 --> 00:36:06,600
You think that they’re ruining Båstad?

463
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,149
I think they should stay at home.

464
00:36:08,150 --> 00:36:09,200
What business to they
have coming down here?

465
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,899
They’re demonstrating
against this tennis match.

466
00:36:11,900 --> 00:36:13,100
Well, it won’t get them anywhere.

467
00:36:13,500 --> 00:36:14,250
It won't do any good?

468
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:17,500
No. Four unfortunate players come here
and they have to suffer for it.

469
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:21,000
How do we play against other nations?

470
00:36:21,500 --> 00:36:22,999
Spain was here playing
football yesterday, right?

471
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,499
It’s the same situation there as in…

472
00:36:24,500 --> 00:36:26,499
What do you think
would have been

473
00:36:26,500 --> 00:36:27,999
the wisest thing to do right now?

474
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:30,999
Well, nothing. Just let them play.

475
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:32,000
Is that what you think?

476
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:33,999
You don’t think it would have

477
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:35,000
been wise to cancel the match?

478
00:36:35,900 --> 00:36:37,999
No, since the whole thing was
decided by lot,

479
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,500
it doesn’t matter who…

480
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,000
Then it has to run its course.

481
00:36:41,500 --> 00:36:42,500
Absolutely! That’s only fair.

482
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,500
Sweden shouldn't have to suffer for it.

483
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:46,999
JOURNALIST, KVÄLLSPOSTEN

484
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:50,000
It’s interesting
that people are coming here,

485
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,999
and it’s sure
to be a very interesting day,

486
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,000
that afterwards there will be
every reason

487
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,000
to shed light on in peace and quiet,

488
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,000
in an objective debate.

489
00:37:02,500 --> 00:37:03,000
Yes, that's quite right.

490
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:07,100
I have nothing against
the demonstrations as such.

491
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:08,999
I'm just afraid it doesn't

492
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:10,500
do much to help the black man.

493
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:13,999
But rather, when all this is over,

494
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:14,999
everyone will go home,

495
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,000
and the black man will be
just as badly off.

496
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:18,500
So, for my part, I’ve suggested
that each demonstrator

497
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:20,499
should carry a collection box

498
00:37:20,500 --> 00:37:20,999
into which they put ten crowns
and see to it

499
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,999
that another forty crowns
make it in there.

500
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:24,499
then we could easily collect, together,

501
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:25,500
the sum of a hundred thousand crowns.

502
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:29,500
And that we could use
to bring over

503
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:32,499
colored children,

504
00:37:32,500 --> 00:37:34,000
orphaned colored children.

505
00:37:34,500 --> 00:37:36,000
That’s what demonstrators
are doing in the case of Vietnam.

506
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:40,999
It’s a good idea,
and it would have been great

507
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,000
if they had done that here, too.

508
00:37:42,500 --> 00:37:43,500
But at the same time,
I’ve suggested

