01:21:16,000 --> 01:21:17,500
there the blacks should have their rights,
as they should everywhere.

1037
01:21:18,500 --> 01:21:20,000
But I mean, they can't do anything.

1038
01:21:21,000 --> 01:21:23,000
If the UN can't, they can't.

1039
01:21:24,000 --> 01:21:25,000
They managed to stop the match anyway.

1040
01:21:25,500 --> 01:21:27,500
Sure, but it doesn't make
any difference.

1041
01:21:29,000 --> 01:21:31,000
I mean, they're going to play anyway.

1042
01:21:32,000 --> 01:21:33,200
It's a tradition.
It's ruined in that sense.

1043
01:21:33,300 --> 01:21:35,500
You saw the demonstration yesterday.

1044
01:21:36,000 --> 01:21:38,000
What did you think was wrong about it?

1045
01:21:39,000 --> 01:21:41,000
I did not see it.

1046
01:21:43,000 --> 01:21:44,499
I was only there for a short while,

1047
01:21:44,500 --> 01:21:45,740
then I drove home again.

1048
01:21:47,000 --> 01:21:48,000
If they had to demonstrate,

1049
01:21:48,500 --> 01:21:50,000
then they could have done it
peacefully.

1050
01:21:51,000 --> 01:21:53,000
And not gotten so violent.

1051
01:21:58,000 --> 01:21:58,749
What do you think about
the demonstration

1052
01:21:58,750 --> 01:21:59,500
yesterday, here in Båstad?

1053
01:22:00,000 --> 01:22:01,000
It was awful.

1054
01:22:03,000 --> 01:22:04,250
It sure was; bloody awful.

1055
01:22:05,500 --> 01:22:06,500
It was ridiculous.

1056
01:22:07,000 --> 01:22:08,500
It was so childish,
like nothing I've ever seen before.

1057
01:22:09,000 --> 01:22:09,500
Why’s that, do you think?

1058
01:22:10,000 --> 01:22:12,500
Well, I’ll tell you; because it’s
absolutely unnecessary

1059
01:22:13,000 --> 01:22:16,000
to demonstrate like that.
I don't understand why.

1060
01:22:16,500 --> 01:22:16,999
You think it was unneccesary?

1061
01:22:17,000 --> 01:22:18,000
Of course it was unnecessary.

1062
01:22:21,500 --> 01:22:23,000
What do you think
of the demonstration yesterday?

1063
01:22:23,500 --> 01:22:23,999
I didn't like it.

1064
01:22:24,000 --> 01:22:25,000
You shouldn’t mix politics with sports.

1065
01:22:26,000 --> 01:22:27,000
Those kids should have stayed home.

1066
01:22:30,500 --> 01:22:31,499
Should politics and
sports be kept separate?

1067
01:22:31,500 --> 01:22:32,000
Yes, definitely.

1068
01:22:32,500 --> 01:22:32,999
Why?

1069
01:22:33,000 --> 01:22:35,000
Well, because if you
can't keep it out of sports,

1070
01:22:35,500 --> 01:22:37,000
you can't keep it out
of anything.

1071
01:22:38,000 --> 01:22:39,500
I feel the same.

1072
01:22:40,000 --> 01:22:42,000
Politics, sports, separate.

1073
01:22:46,500 --> 01:22:49,000
Why have so many people
gathered here today?

1074
01:22:50,000 --> 01:22:50,999
Well, I'll tell you

1075
01:22:51,000 --> 01:22:51,999
we followed you here.

1076
01:22:52,000 --> 01:22:54,000
We thought you belonged to
that group, see.

1077
01:22:54,500 --> 01:22:55,999
We spotted you along the way,

1078
01:22:56,000 --> 01:22:57,500
And saw that you were headed
up to Ekmans,

1079
01:22:58,000 --> 01:22:59,499
so we drove into town

1080
01:22:59,500 --> 01:23:01,000
and gathered some people together.

1081
01:23:02,000 --> 01:23:02,700
You were going to beat us up?

1082
01:23:02,900 --> 01:23:03,599
No, not beat you up,

1083
01:23:03,600 --> 01:23:04,999
but if that gang had been up at Ekmans,

1084
01:23:05,000 --> 01:23:06,999
then we would have stood there

1085
01:23:07,000 --> 01:23:08,000
and stopped them from leaving.

1086
01:23:08,500 --> 01:23:09,999
But unfortunately they ran off

1087
01:23:10,000 --> 01:23:11,000
last night or this afternoon.

1088
01:23:13,000 --> 01:23:15,000
I agree with the lady here,
that’s absolutely true.

1089
01:23:16,000 --> 01:23:16,999
We think they should

1090
01:23:17,000 --> 01:23:18,000
have been forced to stay on,

1091
01:23:18,500 --> 01:23:20,000
for at least one more night.

1092
01:23:21,500 --> 01:23:22,499
What for?

1093
01:23:22,500 --> 01:23:23,999
They ought to suffer

1094
01:23:24,000 --> 01:23:25,000
some kind of punishment.

1095
01:23:27,000 --> 01:23:28,499
I think they must have

1096
01:23:28,500 --> 01:23:29,500
been very scared up there.

1097
01:23:30,500 --> 01:23:31,499
Why else would they have run

1098
01:23:31,500 --> 01:23:32,500
outside and hidden in the bushes?

1099
01:23:33,000 --> 01:23:33,999
As soon as the people came up there,

1100
01:23:34,000 --> 01:23:34,999
they ran off, out into the bushes,

1101
01:23:35,000 --> 01:23:35,999
and they were huddled out there
until we left again.

1102
01:23:36,000 --> 01:23:37,499
And that's how they've
been carrying on all night.

1103
01:23:37,500 --> 01:23:38,500
We were up there with flashlights.

1104
01:23:40,000 --> 01:23:41,999
They were afraid.
Just terribly afraid.

1105
01:23:42,000 --> 01:23:43,999
Did something happen yesterday?

1106
01:23:44,000 --> 01:23:45,499
I wasn’t here in the evening,
so I don’t know.

1107
01:23:45,500 --> 01:23:47,000
But there were a lot of cars
driving around here

1108
01:23:48,000 --> 01:23:49,000
People were aggressive.

1109
01:23:51,000 --> 01:23:52,500
Very aggressive.

1110
01:23:53,200 --> 01:23:55,000
Why do you think
they demonstrated?

1111
01:23:57,000 --> 01:23:58,500
They don’t know what they’re doing.

1112
01:24:02,000 --> 01:24:02,800
Just a bunch of idiots.

1113
01:24:04,900 --> 01:24:05,500
Brats. Cowards.

1114
01:24:07,200 --> 01:24:07,750
Why do you say that?

1115
01:24:08,000 --> 01:24:09,000
Why they're cowards?

1116
01:24:10,000 --> 01:24:12,200
If they weren't cowards
they would have stayed.

1117
01:24:13,500 --> 01:24:14,999
They’re all well-off,
too, most of them.

1118
01:24:15,000 --> 01:24:15,999
They live here in the summer.

1119
01:24:16,000 --> 01:24:17,250
They ought to behave themselves.

1120
01:24:19,000 --> 01:24:20,400
Why shouldn't one mix
sports with politics?

1121
01:24:22,500 --> 01:24:25,500
They’re two different things,
completely different.

1122
01:24:26,750 --> 01:24:27,200
In what way?

1123
01:24:30,000 --> 01:24:31,999
Well, you shouldn’t…
I can’t explain it,

1124
01:24:32,000 --> 01:24:34,000
but they shouldn't mix
sports and politics.

1125
01:24:34,500 --> 01:24:37,000
Do you know why
they were demonstrating?

1126
01:24:38,000 --> 01:24:40,499
The thing is,
they should go down there

1127
01:24:40,500 --> 01:24:41,500
instead of demonstrating here.

1128
01:24:42,000 --> 01:24:43,000
They’ve only got two players
down here, after all.

1129
01:24:45,000 --> 01:24:47,000
They shouldn’t demonstrate against them;

1130
01:24:47,500 --> 01:24:49,000
in that case they should take up politics,

1131
01:24:49,500 --> 01:24:50,999
not against the players down here.

1132
01:24:51,000 --> 01:24:52,499
They can take it up to the government

1133
01:24:52,500 --> 01:24:53,999
in Stockholm and talk about it
up there instead.

1134
01:24:54,000 --> 01:24:54,999
And then we’re going to vote
for the right party down here,

1135
01:24:55,000 --> 01:24:56,500
so we don’t have
any of those demonstrations.

1136
01:24:57,000 --> 01:24:58,500
Which party is the right one?

1137
01:24:58,600 --> 01:24:59,499
Well, the Conservatives are,
for me anyway.

1138
01:24:59,500 --> 01:25:01,000
I'm not afraid to admit it.

1139
01:25:03,000 --> 01:25:04,499
You’re trying to get ahold

1140
01:25:04,500 --> 01:25:05,499
of the demonstrators?

1141
01:25:05,500 --> 01:25:07,500
Sure, why not shut them up
in there for a while?

1142
01:25:08,000 --> 01:25:09,000
What do the police have to
say about that?

1143
01:25:10,000 --> 01:25:10,999
I don't care.

1144
01:25:11,000 --> 01:25:11,999
We're not going to do anything to them.

1145
01:25:12,000 --> 01:25:12,750
Absolutely nothing.

1146
01:25:14,000 --> 01:25:15,749
We can show them how to
demonstrate properly;

1147
01:25:15,750 --> 01:25:17,000
calmly and peacefully, not like they did -

1148
01:25:18,000 --> 01:25:20,999
coming at the police with iron bars

1149
01:25:21,000 --> 01:25:21,999
and rocks and what have you.

1150
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:24,000
They got off scot-free.

1151
01:25:24,750 --> 01:25:25,999
We had every opportunity last night

1152
01:25:26,000 --> 01:25:26,999
to destroy that building up there,

1153
01:25:27,000 --> 01:25:28,000
but we didn’t do anything.

1154
01:25:28,500 --> 01:25:30,000
We didn’t even touch a single
blade of grass up there,

1155
01:25:31,000 --> 01:25:31,999
Have the police been here?

1156
01:25:32,000 --> 01:25:33,500
Yes, there’s been plenty of police.

1157
01:25:33,000 --> 01:25:33,999
What did they want?

1158
01:25:34,000 --> 01:25:35,000
They just looked around.

1159
01:25:35,500 --> 01:25:36,000
Was that wrong?

1160
01:25:37,000 --> 01:25:38,500
No, it wasn't wrong...

1161
01:25:42,000 --> 01:25:45,000
Everyone has a right to protection.

1162
01:25:47,500 --> 01:25:49,499
How far do you think
the police should go?

1163
01:25:49,500 --> 01:25:50,250
Should they shoot?

1164
01:25:51,000 --> 01:25:53,199
No,
but there are excellent water cannons,

1165
01:25:53,200 --> 01:25:54,200
stuff like that they can use.

1166
01:25:54,900 --> 01:25:55,900
Did you see the demonstration?

1167
01:25:56,200 --> 01:25:58,000
No, I didn’t unfortunately.

1168
01:25:59,000 --> 01:26:00,000
…they were going to ruin

1169
01:26:00,500 --> 01:26:02,000
the whole damn tennis court down there.

1170
01:26:02,500 --> 01:26:04,399
And they were going to ruin things for
the white devil.

1171
01:26:04,400 --> 01:26:06,000
There was a black guy here
declaring that.

1172
01:26:09,500 --> 01:26:11,500
So there's proof of that.

1173
01:26:12,250 --> 01:26:12,900
Why do you think he thought that?

1174
01:26:14,000 --> 01:26:15,550
Well, I don't know.

1175
01:26:16,000 --> 01:26:17,499
But that guy was going to university

1176
01:26:17,500 --> 01:26:19,000
in Stockholm or in Uppsala,

1177
01:26:21,000 --> 01:26:23,500
he had money from the Swedish state

1178
01:26:25,000 --> 01:26:27,000
to go to school here,
and have his living costs paid for.

1179
01:26:29,000 --> 01:26:30,499
And he comes down here

1180
01:26:30,500 --> 01:26:31,500
and ruins things for us,

1181
01:26:32,000 --> 01:26:34,000
comparing us to Ian Smith and all them.

1182
01:26:34,500 --> 01:26:36,000
I don’t think that’s fair to us…

1183
01:26:38,500 --> 01:26:40,999
And for people like that
to act like hooligans…

1184
01:26:41,000 --> 01:26:42,499
why, that just ruins things
for all young people.

1185
01:26:42,500 --> 01:26:45,000
The clique that gets seen,
they’re the ones that ruin things.

1186
01:26:46,000 --> 01:26:49,000
Then it’s the decent kids
that get blamed for it.

1187
01:26:51,000 --> 01:26:52,499
We’ve been over to see Henry Swaving

1188
01:26:52,500 --> 01:26:53,999
and signed a list that he's going

1189
01:26:54,000 --> 01:26:54,999
to send the government,

1190
01:26:55,000 --> 01:26:56,249
that the police should be given
greater authority

1191
01:26:56,250 --> 01:26:58,000
when it comes to these
kinds of demonstrations.

1192
01:26:59,000 --> 01:27:00,250
"Greater authority" -
what does that mean?

1193
01:27:00,500 --> 01:27:02,999
Well, to be able to respond
with a firmer hand,

1194
01:27:03,000 --> 01:27:03,999
when it's really necessary.

1195
01:27:04,000 --> 01:27:05,499
And it is necessary sometimes,

1196
01:27:05,500 --> 01:27:06,200
as we just saw.

1197
01:27:06,700 --> 01:27:07,200
Do the rest of you feel that way, too?

1198
01:27:07,300 --> 01:27:08,000
Y E S!

1199
01:27:09,300 --> 01:27:11,000
You’ve drawn up a petition
to the government.

1200
01:27:11,500 --> 01:27:13,199
What does it say?

1201
01:27:13,200 --> 01:27:14,200
HENRY SWAVING,
GOLD MERCHANT

1202
01:27:14,500 --> 01:27:15,000
Here's what it says.

1203
01:27:15,250 --> 01:27:16,999
Due to the chaos that took place,

1204
01:27:17,000 --> 01:27:18,750
and I am in no way a leader

1205
01:27:19,000 --> 01:27:21,000
of the Båstad residents.

1206
01:27:22,500 --> 01:27:25,000
I am just a citizen
who wants to help other citizens.

1207
01:27:26,000 --> 01:27:27,500
This petition consists of the following:

1208
01:27:28,500 --> 01:27:30,500
We, the undersigned
residents of Båstad,

1209
01:27:31,500 --> 01:27:33,499
have looked on in dismay at the events

1210
01:27:33,500 --> 01:27:35,000
that took place in our town

1211
01:27:36,000 --> 01:27:38,000
in conjunction with the demonstrations

1212
01:27:39,000 --> 01:27:41,000
that were held here on 2 May 1968,

1213
01:27:41,500 --> 01:27:42,499
when Sweden was supposed

1214
01:27:42,500 --> 01:27:44,000
to meet Rhodesia in a tennis match.

1215
01:27:45,000 --> 01:27:48,000
The police made worthy
attempts to keep order.

1216
01:27:49,000 --> 01:27:50,999
Unfortunately,
they lacked the authority

1217
01:27:51,000 --> 01:27:52,500
to use the necessary means
that could have

1218
01:27:53,000 --> 01:27:55,000
effectively put a stop to the hooliganism.

1219
01:27:56,200 --> 01:27:58,500
Therefore,
we petition the government forthwith

1220
01:27:59,200 --> 01:28:01,000
to provide the police command

1221
01:28:01,700 --> 01:28:04,000
with such authority.
If this does not happen,

1222
01:28:04,700 --> 01:28:07,000
we fear for what we might experience

1223
01:28:07,500 --> 01:28:09,000
in our town in the future.

1224
01:28:10,500 --> 01:28:12,000
How far do you feel the police should go?

1225
01:28:13,500 --> 01:28:16,000
How much authority should they have,
do you think?

1226
01:28:17,000 --> 01:28:18,499
I can't comment on what authority

1227
01:28:18,500 --> 01:28:20,000
the police should be given

1228
01:28:21,500 --> 01:28:26,000
if hooligans attack a community;

1229
01:28:28,000 --> 01:28:30,000
That's for the government to comment on.

1230
01:28:31,000 --> 01:28:32,500
Even if it means being armed?

1231
01:28:34,000 --> 01:28:34,999
Then the government should

1232
01:28:35,000 --> 01:28:35,999
make absolutely sure

1233
01:28:36,000 --> 01:28:36,999
no such elements

1234
01:28:37,000 --> 01:28:38,000
are allowed into the country,

1235
01:28:38,200 --> 01:28:39,200
so it doesn't lead to armed conflict.

1236
01:28:40,000 --> 01:28:41,499
Because Sweden hasn't gone

1237
01:28:41,500 --> 01:28:44,000
completely communist yet,
I hope.

1238
01:28:47,000 --> 01:28:48,499
There’s quite a brisk flow of traffic

1239
01:28:48,500 --> 01:28:50,500
out to an area over by Hovs Hallar,

1240
01:28:51,000 --> 01:28:52,499
where some demonstrators are

1241
01:28:52,500 --> 01:28:53,499
supposed to be holed up.

1242
01:28:53,500 --> 01:28:54,500
Do you know anything about that?

1243
01:28:55,000 --> 01:28:57,000
Yes, some of them were still there.

1244
01:28:59,000 --> 01:29:02,500
These black groups,
that belong to the FNL,

1245
01:29:03,000 --> 01:29:06,499
who were very aggressive at the gates.

1246
01:29:06,500 --> 01:29:08,000
Båstad residents got wind of this

1247
01:29:09,000 --> 01:29:12,000
and really wanted to get ahold
of those... types.

1248
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:16,499
Yesterday there were at least

1249
01:29:16,500 --> 01:29:18,000
a hundred youths there.

1250
01:29:20,500 --> 01:29:22,000
Then I went over there myself

1251
01:29:24,500 --> 01:29:27,000
with the editor of the Kvällsposten,

1252
01:29:29,750 --> 01:29:31,000
Buhre, his name is.

1253
01:29:36,000 --> 01:29:40,000
Birger Buhr. Then, after a
five or six minute discussion

1254
01:29:40,500 --> 01:29:43,000
between Birger Buhr
and this demonstrator,

1255
01:29:44,000 --> 01:29:45,499
it looked like it was

1256
01:29:45,500 --> 01:29:47,000
really going to turn into a lynching.

1257
01:29:47,500 --> 01:29:48,499
Then one of the police officers

1258
01:29:48,500 --> 01:29:50,499
asked if I wouldn’t get involved,

1259
01:29:50,500 --> 01:29:53,000
to try and calm the whole thing down.

1260
01:29:54,500 --> 01:29:56,000
So I showed a bit of aggressiveness,

1261
01:29:57,500 --> 01:29:59,999
and told off a few of

1262
01:30:00,000 --> 01:30:01,000
those stupid demonstrators

1263
01:30:02,500 --> 01:30:06,000
and finally I said:
Come on, people of Båstad,

1264
01:30:06,500 --> 01:30:08,000
let's not be as disorderly

1265
01:30:09,500 --> 01:30:11,000
as these rowdy people.

1266
01:30:12,000 --> 01:30:13,999
Let’s go home and I’ll treat
everyone to some refreshment.

1267
01:30:14,000 --> 01:30:15,900
And with that,
everyone came along quietly.

1268
01:30:17,000 --> 01:30:18,499
KLING: NOW WE REALLY
HAVE TO STOP AND THINK

1269
01:30:18,500 --> 01:30:21,000
Has the police commissioner
been informed about what happened?

1270
01:30:22,000 --> 01:30:25,499
It was through him
that I got the information I have,

1271
01:30:25,500 --> 01:30:26,500
beyond what I learned through the

1272
01:30:27,000 --> 01:30:28,000
southern Swedish press.

1273
01:30:30,000 --> 01:30:31,500
And may I ask you then whether

1274
01:30:32,500 --> 01:30:35,500
he has changed your view

1275
01:30:36,500 --> 01:30:39,000
of how similar incidents should be handled?

1276
01:30:41,000 --> 01:30:42,499
The police commissioner

1277
01:30:42,500 --> 01:30:44,500
has clearly stated that from his point of view,

1278
01:30:49,000 --> 01:30:53,000
a greater commitment of personnel

1279
01:30:55,000 --> 01:30:58,499
could have prevented any violence

1280
01:30:58,500 --> 01:30:59,500
from breaking out altogether.

1281
01:31:00,000 --> 01:31:01,999
In the press the following day

1282
01:31:02,000 --> 01:31:03,999
it was intimated
that the police are going

1283
01:31:04,000 --> 01:31:04,999
to be given greater authority.

1284
01:31:05,000 --> 01:31:06,000
Would you care to comment on that?

1285
01:31:07,500 --> 01:31:09,000
It was Kling who said it,

1286
01:31:09,500 --> 01:31:10,999
that the National Police Board

1287
01:31:11,000 --> 01:31:12,499
would be given greater authority.

1288
01:31:12,500 --> 01:31:13,499
I find it pretty shameful

1289
01:31:13,500 --> 01:31:14,499
that that's the first thing
Kling has to say

1290
01:31:14,500 --> 01:31:16,000
about this whole business
with Rhodesia.

1291
01:31:17,990 --> 01:31:18,899
One would expect that he,

1292
01:31:18,900 --> 01:31:20,100
as the government's expert
on legal issues,

1293
01:31:21,900 --> 01:31:24,000
ought to be able
to comment on the fact

1294
01:31:28,000 --> 01:31:29,499
that we have signed up to a boycott

1295
01:31:29,500 --> 01:31:31,500
against Rhodesia in the UN,

1296
01:31:32,000 --> 01:31:33,500
about the breaking of the pledge we made

1297
01:31:34,000 --> 01:31:36,500
to Rhodesia's colored population,

1298
01:31:37,000 --> 01:31:39,000
not to support the Smith regime,

1299
01:31:42,500 --> 01:31:44,999
and about the crime that allowing
a tennis match against Rhodesia

1300
01:31:45,000 --> 01:31:46,000
within Sweden entails.

1301
01:31:47,000 --> 01:31:48,499
Everything else,

1302
01:31:48,500 --> 01:31:49,999
the confrontations that broke out here

1303
01:31:50,000 --> 01:31:51,500
before the match,

1304
01:31:52,000 --> 01:31:53,999
are seocndary in comparison

1305
01:31:54,000 --> 01:31:55,000
to the moral treachery that it involves

1306
01:31:56,500 --> 01:31:59,000
to formally allow the Smith regime

1307
01:31:59,500 --> 01:32:02,000
to gain recognition by playing
a national match against Rhodesia.

1308
01:32:03,000 --> 01:32:04,500
And that’s where I think

1309
01:32:05,000 --> 01:32:06,999
Kling should have been upset,

1310
01:32:07,000 --> 01:32:08,000
instead of coming along

1311
01:32:09,500 --> 01:32:11,999
afterwards and being upset
about secondary consequences.

1312
01:32:12,000 --> 01:32:12,999
If the police were to use

1313
01:32:13,000 --> 01:32:14,500
harsher methods in the future,

1314
01:32:15,000 --> 01:32:17,250
what do you think that would mean?

1315
01:32:18,200 --> 01:32:19,500
It's a very alarming development.

1316
01:32:20,000 --> 01:32:21,999
But it seems as if things
are headed in that direction.

1317
01:32:22,000 --> 01:32:23,500
You can see it in a lot
of different areas,

1318
01:32:24,000 --> 01:32:26,000
if you look at the subway
in Stockholm now,

1319
01:32:26,500 --> 01:32:27,999
and the new city centre

1320
01:32:28,000 --> 01:32:29,000
that's been built for banks and cars,

1321
01:32:30,000 --> 01:32:31,999
not for people.

1322
01:32:32,000 --> 01:32:32,999
That causes anxiety,

1323
01:32:33,000 --> 01:32:34,250
because people want to
have somewhere to go.

1324
01:32:35,000 --> 01:32:37,250
But then instead of grappling
with the root causes,

1325
01:32:39,000 --> 01:32:41,049
they just try to crush

1326
01:32:41,050 --> 01:32:42,999
any expressions of discontent

1327
01:32:43,000 --> 01:32:44,950
through TV coverage

1328
01:32:45,000 --> 01:32:46,000
and tougher police action.

1329
01:32:47,000 --> 01:32:47,999
I think we face a period of difficult

1330
01:32:48,000 --> 01:32:49,000
re-evaluation in this country,

1331
01:32:49,500 --> 01:32:51,000
and throughout the West,

1332
01:32:52,000 --> 01:32:53,000
and that it could be the beginning

1333
01:32:54,250 --> 01:32:56,000
of a very unpleasant development,

1334
01:32:57,000 --> 01:32:57,999
instead of facing up

1335
01:32:58,000 --> 01:32:59,000
to the new situation,

1336
01:33:02,000 --> 01:33:05,000
they try to crush
expressions of dissatisfaction.

1337
01:33:06,000 --> 01:33:07,500
KLING ON THE RIOTS:
STOP THE HOOLIGANS

1338
01:33:08,500 --> 01:33:09,999
I heard now
that justice minister Kling

1339
01:33:10,000 --> 01:33:11,000
made a statement

1340
01:33:11,500 --> 01:33:13,000
in Svenska Dagladet,

1341
01:33:13,500 --> 01:33:16,000
where he called us
a bunch of hooligans.

1342
01:33:18,500 --> 01:33:21,000
I find this to be a very
worrying situation and tendency,

1343
01:33:22,500 --> 01:33:24,000
because it reveals the enormous lack

1344
01:33:24,200 --> 01:33:26,500
of information that the public and press,

1345
01:33:27,000 --> 01:33:28,999
and everyone else has

1346
01:33:29,000 --> 01:33:31,000
about who the demonstrators are.

1347
01:33:32,000 --> 01:33:34,499
I think it’s really awful

1348
01:33:34,500 --> 01:33:37,000
to see the role of the press
in this respect,

1349
01:33:38,000 --> 01:33:41,000
how they continue
to fan these prejudices,

1350
01:33:41,500 --> 01:33:42,999
how they’re engaging
in a persecution propaganda

1351
01:33:43,000 --> 01:33:44,000
against the demonstrators.

1352
01:33:45,000 --> 01:33:47,250
The combination of increased police authority,

1353
01:33:48,000 --> 01:33:49,000
increased police violence,

1354
01:33:49,500 --> 01:33:50,999
and increased politicization
of the police

1355
01:33:51,000 --> 01:33:52,000
is what I find to be
the most frightening.

1356
01:33:53,500 --> 01:33:55,000
When you can see
Sven Davidson,

1357
01:33:55,500 --> 01:33:56,500
who is just beneath Wallenberg,

1358
01:33:57,000 --> 01:33:57,999
giving orders to the police,

1359
01:33:58,000 --> 01:33:58,999
who they should attack,

1360
01:33:59,000 --> 01:33:59,999
where they should be put in,

1361
01:34:00,000 --> 01:34:00,999
and at the same time the police
just say

1362
01:34:01,000 --> 01:34:01,999
they have no opinion on this,

1363
01:34:02,000 --> 01:34:03,500
but are controlled
by a political force,

1364
01:34:04,000 --> 01:34:05,499
then I think it's dangerous

1365
01:34:05,500 --> 01:34:07,000
to give them more authority.

1366
01:34:08,000 --> 01:34:10,000
Instead they ought to examine

1367
01:34:11,000 --> 01:34:12,499
what exactly the police
are supposed to defend,

1368
01:34:12,500 --> 01:34:13,499
what role they should have,

1369
01:34:13,500 --> 01:34:14,250
and not just let them

1370
01:34:15,000 --> 01:34:16,000
be politicized freely.

1371
01:34:16,200 --> 01:34:17,000
That’s what Kling should be doing.

1372
01:34:18,000 --> 01:34:19,999
The Swedish Tennis Association
issued a communiqué

1373
01:34:20,000 --> 01:34:22,000
that read more or less as follows:

1374
01:34:24,000 --> 01:34:26,000
We will not reveal where
the Rhodesia match

1375
01:34:26,500 --> 01:34:28,499
